By: CompareCards | May 11, 2017
Deciding which rewards card is best may vary based on how you usually spend your money. For example, if you spend a lot on groceries and gas, the Blue Cash Preferred Card from American Express  is probably your best choice. But if you're simply looking for a credit card with a great flat rewards rate on every purchase, the Citi Double Cash is an excellent option.









