Bank of America | BA Master Credit Card Trust II Static Pool | Disclosure









BA Master Credit Card Trust II Static Pool Information
Please read this important notice before proceeding.
Web Site Content: This Web site is operated by Bank of America, National Association ("BANA") and serves  as a repository for selected historical performance information—referred to as static pool information—relating to the Master Trust II Portfolio. The Master Trust II Portfolio is comprised of receivables owned by BA Master Credit Card Trust II.

The information contained on this Web site is accurate as of the date posted.  BANA has undertaken no obligation, and has assumed no responsibility, to update any information contained on this Web site for facts or events arising subsequent to the date any such information is posted.

No Offer or Solicitation: No information contained on this Web site constitutes an offer to sell or the solicitation of an offer to buy any securities. 

As of December 31, 2014, all of the accounts relating to the receivables in the Master Trust II Portfolio were 60 or more months past the date on which they were originated.  The origination date for each such account is the date on which the account was opened.  Additional accounts were last added to the Master Trust II Portfolio on January 7, 2010.  No accounts originated after December 31, 2009 are currently included in the Master Trust II Portfolio and no related static pool information is being provided here.












		
		
			Bank of America, N.A. Member FDIC.
			© 2017 Bank of America Corporation. All rights reserved.
		
		

